ility.\\n- The FX chain order is correct: Input → Delay → Reverb → Freeze → Comb.\\n- The signal flow uses `SelectX.ar` for clean branching and `LocalIn`/`LocalOut` for the feedback delay.\\n\\n## Completeness\\nAll required components are present:\\n- `sw_sampler_fx` SynthDef includes all four FX stages.\\n- Damping and decay controls are wired into the DSP graph.\\n- Python integration tests (`tests/test_sampler_effects.py`) provide exhaustive declarative verification of the SCD source (UGens, arguments, defaults, clipping, and order).\\n- SC-side runtime tests (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sampler_effects.scd`) verify non-silent output, freeze-toggle behavior, and the 61.74 Hz spectral peak.\\n\\n## Consistency\\nThe code follows established project conventions:\\n- SynthDef naming and bus assignments (stereo at 16) match the Sampler PRD.\\n- DSP logic uses standard SuperCollider patterns (`CombC`, `LPF`, `SelectX`).\\n- Python tests utilize the established regex-based source validation pattern.\\n\\n## Security\\nNo security vulnerabilities or secret leaks were identified. The changes are strictly DSP and testing logic.\\n\\n## Quality\\nThe code quality is high:\\n- Extensive range clipping in the SynthDef ensures numerical stability (e.g., `cbDecay` clipped to 0.05..10.0s).\\n- The `cbDampCutoff` formula provides a musically useful transition from \\\"bright\\\" to \\\"woody\\\" resonance.\\n- SC-side tests include automated RMS and FFT-based magnitude checks for objective verification.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- None.\\n\\n## Verdict: PASS\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\nThe implementation is solid and well-verified. The candidate hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be pre-existing and correctly wired in both `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`.\\n\",\"file_path\":\"sdp/verification/t-002@20260425t183959zd-verify.md\"}}\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260425T183959Zd_1777146814.log:sdp/runner.log:1981:{\"type\":\"message\",\"timestam