teria:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:05.974Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'll examine the most recent commit with `git show HEAD` to verify which files were included and confirm if\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:05.975Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" `progress.md` was inadvertently modified.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:06.016Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1776398766016_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Checking the latest commit.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"git show HEAD\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:06.291Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1776398766016_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"commit e05d4ceb8fbc88cea4589e6d99d3a69b770f07ef (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDate:   Thu Apr 16 21:05:56 2026 -0700\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    verify(T-024@20260416T181925Z): independent verification pass — PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md b/sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nnew file mode 100644\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nindex 0000000..8a05d81\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n--- /dev/null\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+++ b/sdp/verification/t-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# Verification Report — T-024 @20260416t181925z-verify.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Date:** 2026-04-17\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Artifacts Reviewed:**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/call_response.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `tests/test_call_response.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `src/cypherclaw/render/events.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `src/cypherclaw/render/role_gate.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Correctness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation of R11 Call-Response Gating correctly transforms the follower's phrase shape based on the leader's realized performance. The logic in `_descend_from_apex` and `_fill` accurately reflects the requirements for complementarity and filling. Specifically:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- When the leader is building (`is_building=True`), the follower's amplitude is reduced and its contour apex is inverted to complement the leader.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- When the leader is pausing (`is_pausing=True`), the follower's amplitude is boosted and its contour apex is reinforced to fill the gap.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Role metadata (`leader`, `follower`, `solo`, `tacet`) is correctly parsed and respected, with the rule only applying to voices explicitly tagged as followers.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Completeness\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The task is complete according to the acceptance criteria:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- `CallResponseRule` implemented in `render/rules/call_response.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Correct transformations for building and pausing states.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Metadata role parsing covers all required keys and values.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Comprehensive test suite in `tests/test_call_response.py` verifies both functional behavior and role-based filtering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation is consistent with other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Tier 1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" render rules in `src/cypherclaw/render/rules/` (e.g., `phrase_arch.py`, `articulation.py`). It uses the shared `Event` data model and follows the `role_is_eligible` contract established in `role_gate.py`. Although `PerformanceIntent` was mentioned in the spec, it is not yet present in the codebase (targeted for T-030), and the use of the `Event` model for these transformations is the correct adaptation for the current project state.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+No security vulnerabilities or unsafe practices were introduced. The implementation consists of pure-function mathematical transformations on local data structures.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The code quality is high, with clear documentation, clean dataclass abstractions, and robust role-parsing logic. The tests use Pearson correlation to verify complementarity, which is a rigorous approach for validating musical behavior.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+The implementation successfully realizes the call-response gating requirement. The adaptation to use the `Event` model in the absence of `PerformanceIntent` is appropriate. Recurring hardening checks for `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be satisfied in the current daemon startup paths.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:12.389Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'll\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T04:06:12.406Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"assistant\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" update `progress.md` to mark T-024 as complete and include the relevant logs, ensuring the SDP\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"delta\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":true}\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\n+codex\\\\\\\\n+The dirty state is entirely generated SDP tracking: progress, run logs, notifications, telemetry, and an untracked canonical T-024 verification report that complements an earlier misnamed report. I’m staging those artifacts now so the tree can be committed and left clean.\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'git add -A' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 109ms:\\\\\\\\n+exec\\\\\\\\n+/bin/zsh -lc 'git status --short' in /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\\\\\n+ succeeded in 0ms:\\\\\\\\n+M  progress.md\\\\\\\\n+M  sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Zb_1776395654.log\\\\\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Zc_1776395895.log\\\\\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260416T181925Z_1776396842.log\\\\\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-023_20260416T181925Z_1776397430.log\\\\\\\\n+A  sdp/logs/Lead_T-025_20260416T181925Z_