./sdp/logs/Verify_T-010_20260416T181925Z_1776384512.log:96:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-17T00:08:37.357Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-010@20260416T181925Z\n\n**Task:** Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-010@20260416t181925z-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-010@20260416T181925Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[a