my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:19:1. **Granular by default, never one-shot.** The sampler is a granular voice with grain size 20–200 ms, density, position scrub, and pitch transpose. "Press button hear sample" is not a use case. Every play is a re-rendering through grains.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:29:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:50:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:54:- `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md` — the rendering layer; sampler events flow through the same RenderPass (R-rules respect `role="sampler"` with grid_locked=False so phrasing applies, but R8 microtiming is dampened on grain-time-scale events).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:97:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:115:| CCS-027 | Surface "currently sampling X" + "playing sample Y from source Z" in `operator_diagnostics.py` and the face/inkplate display. | MUST | T2 | - `operator_diagnostics.py::sampler_status() -> dict` returns `{capture_active: bool, capture_seconds_buffered: int, last_capture: dict, current_playback: list[dict]}`<br/>- daemon writes `/tmp/sampler_state.json` every 1 sec for the diagnostic to read<br/>- face/inkplate renderers gain a one-line "♫ sampling room" / "♫ memory: <self/2026-04-25>" banner<br/>- tests verify state-file schema and diagnostic output format |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:117:| CCS-029 | Implement `metrics::sampler_event_count_per_piece` and `metrics::sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` for the metrics-CI gate. | MUST | T1 | - integrated with the existing render `metrics.py` (CCH-014)<br/>- per-piece event count is recorded and surfaced in operator diagnostics<br/>- library:self ratio is computed across the last 50 pieces; healthy band 1.5..3.0<br/>- tests verify metric computation and threshold reporting |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:118:| CCS-030 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | MUST | T1 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |
