my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:5:CypherClaw already composes legible music: score trees, section functions, production profiles, genre strategies, SenseWeave mappings. But the path from composed score to synthesized audio still renders too rigidly. Phrases don't breathe. Repeated motifs don't vary. Silence is a byproduct of scheduling rather than an intentional voice. Sensors occasionally read like one-to-one controllers rather than shaping aggregate intent. The result is the "almost-human" failure mode: structurally competent, expressively flat.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:9:This PRD installs a dedicated **rendering layer** — a compiler pass between composition (score-tree) and synthesis (SuperCollider) — that translates score structure into correlated, intentional deviations in timing, dynamics, articulation, and silence. The architecture is KTH-rule-system-style: a stack of ordered, pure-function rules, each reading score features and emitting event-level deviations, each toggleable and quantity-adjustable, each leaving provenance on every event so authors can ablate and debug.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:23:**In scope:** a new rendering stage between composition and synthesis; an Event/PerformanceIntent/SectionEnvelope data model with rule-stack provenance; a 12-rule render stack (R1–R12); a seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds; a replay harness; a rule-ablation debugger; a metrics-CI gate with anti-pattern detection; a performance-worm diagnostic; a bounded sensor-to-intent aggregation matrix.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:31:- Replacement of existing composition, production-course, or synthesis work. This layer sits *above* synthesis and *below* composition — it renders what the composer emits.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:35:**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCH-001..CCH-010).** Data model, seeded-RNG plumbing, replay harness, rule-ablation debugger. At end of phase, existing pieces render bit-identically through the new pipeline with no rules active — just plumbing.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:43:**Metrics-CI Gate + Diagnostics (CCH-034..CCH-040).** Metric battery, anti-pattern detection, performance-worm logger, CI integration, audio-rendered cross-check, provenance in exported audio metadata, listener-review workflow. Runs in parallel with rule-stack build-out; most checks land alongside the rule they validate.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:48:- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` — the score-tree composer this layer renders from.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:54:- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/` package:
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:55:  - `render/events.py` — Event, PerformanceIntent, SectionEnvelope, IntentTag, Role dataclasses
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:56:  - `render/seed.py` — per-stage sub-seed derivation, replay harness
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:57:  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:58:  - `render/pass_.py` — RenderPass framework, ordered rule stack, ablation support
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:59:  - `render/features.py` — partitura-backed phrase/harmonic feature extraction
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:60:  - `render/replay.py` — bit-identical (score, seed, delta_track) → performed_part reproduction
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:61:  - `render/worm.py` — performance-worm logger and convex-hull diagnostic
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:62:  - `render/metrics.py` — IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR, GS, pitch H1, LZ76, tempo autocorrelation, silence coverage
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:63:  - `render/antipatterns.py` — quantization-ghosting, dynamic-compression, motif-ossification, random-as-expression, symmetric-arc-uncanny, dead-silence detectors
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:69:- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_render_*.py` — per-rule, role-filter, replay, ablation, metric, anti-pattern tests
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:75:| CCH-001 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:76:| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:77:| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:78:| CCH-004 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | MUST | T1 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:79:| CCH-005 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | MUST | T1 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:80:| CCH-006 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | MUST | T1 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:82:| CCH-008 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | MUST | T1 | - OSC bundle schema documented in `my-claw/docs/render-osc-schema.md`<br/>- `music_tracker_runtime.py` serializes Event fields into Pbind-compatible dictionaries preserving rule_stack and seed_path<br/>- synth side (reference SC file under `my-claw/supercollider/render_contract.scd`) demonstrates reading and ignoring unknown keys gracefully<br/>- tests verify round-trip of a sample phrase through serialize → parse preserves all fields |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:83:| CCH-009 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | MUST | T1 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- delta_track is persisted as JSON per run alongside audio output<br/>- tests verify: re-render with same inputs produces identical Event sequence (hash match) including all timing, velocity, and articulation values |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:84:| CCH-010 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | MUST | T1 | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:85:| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:86:| CCH-012 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:87:| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:88:| CCH-014 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:89:| CCH-015 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:90:| CCH-016 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:91:| CCH-017 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:92:| CCH-018 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:93:| CCH-019 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:94:| CCH-020 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | MUST | T1 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:95:| CCH-021 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | MUST | T1 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:96:| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:97:| CCH-023 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:99:| CCH-025 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:104:| CCH-030 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:108:| CCH-034 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | MUST | T1 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:109:| CCH-035 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | MUST | T1 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:110:| CCH-036 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | MUST | T1 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:111:| CCH-037 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | MUST | T1 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where applicable (withhold-tagged phrases allow lower velocity σ)<br/>- tests verify a deliberately broken render fails the gate and a healthy render passes |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:112:| CCH-038 | Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. | SHOULD | T2 | - offline renderer produces 5-minute proxy audio for fixture pieces<br/>- librosa self-similarity matrix + Foote novelty curve extracted<br/>- symbolic novelty peaks (from CCH-034) must align with audio novelty peaks within ±500 ms<br/>- catches cases where symbolic metrics look fine but synthesis flattens expression |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:113:| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:114:| CCH-040 | Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. | SHOULD | T2 | - `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` describes cadence, how to ablate a rule, how to attach a review note<br/>- weekly review log at `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` with template entries (piece, date, felt-wrong symptom, suspected rule, ablation result, action)<br/>- tests: doc and template exist and link to the ablation CLI from CCH-010 |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:118:1. End-to-end: existing pieces render bit-identically through the new pipeline when all rules are disabled (Phase 1 plumbing is transparent).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:120:3. Grid-locked voices (ostinato, perc) emerge from full-stack render with timing_deviation_ms == 0 — machine identity preserved.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:122:5. Silence Budget (R10) enforces ≥100 ms silence at every phrase boundary on melodic voices in a 2-minute rendered fixture.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:124:7. Sensor Aggregation (R12) passes the reverse-engineer test: no single sensor correlates > 0.85 with any single synth parameter over a 5-minute rendered run with recorded sensor stream.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:127:10. Metric battery + anti-pattern detectors integrated into CI; a deliberate regression (e.g., microtiming σ bumped to 50 ms, velocity range compressed to 5) fails the gate.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:129:12. Rule-stack provenance present in every exported `.render.json` sidecar.
